  "text": "There has been prior work on trellis quantization schemes for beamformer design [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Euclidean distance trellis quantizers have been used to quantize large-dimensional signals in [CITATION_3] . Further, the connection between beamformer quantization and noncoherent trellis codes was first pointed out in [CITATION_4] and extended in [CITATION_5] , [CITATION_6] . But the path metric for the trellis search in [CITATION_7] - [CITATION_8] is ad hoc, resulting in a suboptimal use of the trellis quantizer. The duality between noncoherent detection and quantization for transmit precoding was pointed out in [CITATION_9] , but the nontrivial trellis codes used in NTCQ outperform the uncoded constellations used in [CITATION_10] .",
